#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:99
msgid "What the IR Looks Like"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:101
msgid ""
"Here are a few examples of `dialect-mir` operations in practice. These are "
"simplified for readability -- the actual printed form includes more metadata."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:104
msgid "**Checked addition** (Rust: `let sum = a + b` where `a, b: i32`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:106
msgid ""
"// mir.checked_add returns a tuple (result, overflow_flag)\n"
"%checked = mir.checked_add %a, %b : i32\n"
"%sum     = mir.extract_field %checked, 0 : mir.tuple<i32, i1>\n"
"%overflowed = mir.extract_field %checked, 1 : mir.tuple<i32, i1>\n"
"mir.assert %overflowed == false, \"attempt to add with overflow\" -> bb1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:114
msgid "**Struct construction and field access** (Rust: `point.x`):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:116
msgid ""
"%point = mir.construct_struct %x, %y : mir.struct<\"Point\", [f32, f32]>\n"
"%x_val = mir.extract_field %point, 0 : mir.struct<\"Point\", [f32, f32]>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:121
msgid "**Shared memory allocation** (the GPU-specific part):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:123
msgid ""
"%shmem = mir.shared_alloc : mir.ptr<f32, mutable, addrspace: 3>\n"
"mir.store %value, %shmem : f32\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:128
msgid "Verification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:130
msgid ""
"Every MIR operation verifies type consistency when constructed. This catches "
"import bugs early -- before they have a chance to propagate through the "
"lowering pipeline and surface as cryptic LLVM errors three passes later."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:134
msgid "Examples of what gets checked:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:136
msgid "`mir.add` verifies that both operands have the same type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:137
msgid "`mir.cond_br` verifies that the condition is `i1` (a boolean)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:138
msgid ""
"`mir.extract_field` verifies that the field index is in bounds and the "
"result type matches the field's type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:140
msgid ""
"`mir.store` verifies that the value type matches the pointee type of the "
"pointer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:143
msgid ""
"`DisjointSlice` accepts only a matching `ThreadIndex`, so the type system "
"checks the device-side index space. Host launch geometry completes the "
"uniqueness proof through `PreparedLaunch<K>` or an unsafe raw-launch "
"obligation. There is no separate disjoint-access compiler pass; the safety "
"comes from these APIs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:150
msgid "The LLVM Dialect -- The LLVM Layer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:152
msgid ""
"The LLVM dialect models LLVM IR as pliron operations. It provides a near-1:1 "
"mapping to textual `.ll` files -- every LLVM instruction has a corresponding "
"pliron operation, and the types map directly to LLVM's type system. The "
"dialect itself (ops, types, attributes, op-interfaces) is defined upstream "
"in the `pliron-llvm` crate; cuda-oxide consumes it and re-exports it through "
"the thin `llvm-export` crate, which also carries the textual `.ll` exporter "
"and a few GPU-specific extensions (named address spaces, a syncscope enum, "
"fp16 bit helpers) that pliron-llvm does not ship."
msgstr ""

