#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:316
msgid ""
"The first column is the Rust struct name in `dialect-nvvm`. The second is "
"what `llvm-export` emits (after the underscore-to-dot transformation). The "
"third is what `llc` produces. You never have to write any of these by hand "
"-- they are generated by `mir-lower` when it sees calls to `cuda-device` "
"intrinsic functions like `thread::index_x()` or `warp::shfl_sync_bfly()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:322
msgid "Verification Strategy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:324
msgid ""
"NVVM operations use minimal structural verification: each operation checks "
"its operand count and result count, and a handful verify result types "
"(thread indexing ops require `i32` results; `tcgen05` loads check exact "
"result counts for their 32-register and 4-register variants)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:329
msgid ""
"This is intentional. NVVM operations are machine-generated by `mir-lower` -- "
"they are never hand-written by users. LLVM's NVPTX backend provides "
"comprehensive type validation downstream. Adding full type checking to every "
"NVVM operation would double the dialect's code size for zero practical "
"benefit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:335
msgid ""
"The GPU architecture requirements (sm_70, sm_90, sm_100) are documented but "
"not enforced at the pliron level. Architecture validation happens later, "
"when `llc` is invoked with a specific `-mcpu=sm_XX` flag. If you use a "
"Hopper intrinsic and target Volta, `llc` will tell you -- loudly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:343
msgid "How the Dialects Interact"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:345
msgid ""
"Here is the lifecycle of a single Rust operation as it passes through all "
"three abstraction levels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:348
msgid ""
"Rust source:   let sum = a + b;        // a, b: f32\n"
"\n"
"dialect-mir:   %sum = mir.add %a, %b : f32\n"
"                ↓  (DialectConversion)\n"
"LLVM dialect:  %v5 = fadd float %v3, %v4\n"
"                ↓  (llvm-export)\n"
"LLVM IR:       %v5 = fadd float %v3, %v4\n"
"                ↓  (llc --mcpu=sm_80)\n"
"PTX:           add.f32 %f3, %f1, %f2;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:360
msgid ""
"The `dialect-mir` → LLVM dialect step is where the interesting work happens: "
"`mir.add` on `f32` becomes `fadd` (floating-point add), while `mir.add` on "
"`i32` becomes `add` (integer add). Checked operations like `mir.checked_add` "
"expand into an `llvm.add`, a constant `i1 false` for the overflow flag, and "
"an `insertvalue` into a struct -- the GPU path omits overflow detection "
"(since GPU integer arithmetic wraps). The lowering pass handles all of these "
"translations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:368
msgid "For GPU-specific operations, `dialect-nvvm` enters the picture:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:370
msgid ""
"Rust source:   let tid = thread::threadIdx_x();\n"
"\n"
"dialect-mir:   %tid = mir.call @cuda_oxide_device_<hash>_thread_index_x()\n"
"                ↓  (DialectConversion, recognizes the intrinsic)\n"
"dialect-nvvm:  %v2 = nvvm.read_ptx_sreg_tid_x : i32\n"
"                ↓  (llvm-export)\n"
"LLVM IR:       %v2 = call i32 @llvm.nvvm.read.ptx.sreg.tid.x() #0\n"
"                ↓  (llc)\n"
"PTX:           mov.u32 %r1, %tid.x;\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:382
msgid ""
"The lowering pass recognizes calls to `cuda_device` intrinsic functions by "
"their fully qualified names (FQDNs) and replaces them with the corresponding "
"`dialect-nvvm` operations. No generic \"function call\" machinery is needed "
"-- the intrinsic becomes a direct hardware instruction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:387
msgid "The Full Picture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:389
msgid ""
"Putting it all together, a compiled kernel body contains a mix of LLVM "
"dialect and `dialect-nvvm` operations:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:392
msgid ""
"llvm.func @vecadd(...) {\n"
"  entry:\n"
"    %tid    = nvvm.read_ptx_sreg_tid_x     // NVVM: thread index\n"
"    %ntid   = nvvm.read_ptx_sreg_ntid_x    // NVVM: block size\n"
"    %ctaid  = nvvm.read_ptx_sreg_ctaid_x   // NVVM: block index\n"
"    %offset = llvm.mul %ctaid, %ntid        // LLVM: integer math\n"
"    %idx    = llvm.add %offset, %tid        // LLVM: integer math\n"
"    %cmp    = llvm.icmp slt %idx, %len      // LLVM: bounds check\n"
"    llvm.cond_br %cmp, bb1, bb2             // LLVM: branch\n"
"  bb1:\n"
"    %p_a    = llvm.gep %a, %idx             // LLVM: pointer arithmetic\n"
"    %val_a  = llvm.load %p_a                // LLVM: memory access\n"
"    %p_b    = llvm.gep %b, %idx\n"
"    %val_b  = llvm.load %p_b\n"
"    %sum    = llvm.fadd %val_a, %val_b      // LLVM: floating-point add\n"
"    %p_c    = llvm.gep %c, %idx\n"
"    llvm.store %sum, %p_c\n"
"    llvm.br bb2\n"
"  bb2:\n"
"    llvm.return void\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:416
msgid ""
"The `dialect-nvvm` operations at the top compute the global thread index. "
"Everything else is standard LLVM dialect -- loads, stores, arithmetic, "
"branches. The export engine serializes all of it into a single `.ll` file, "
"and `llc` compiles it to PTX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../compiler/mlir-dialects.md:423
msgid ""
"For how these dialects are connected by the lowering pass, see [The Lowering "
"Pipeline](lowering-pipeline.md)."
msgstr ""
